1
00:00:01,445 --> 00:00:06,833
(gentle music) (hooves clattering)

2
00:00:45,345 --> 00:00:47,742
- Hannah, the moon is so bright tonight.

3
00:00:47,777 --> 00:00:50,280
- [Both] And this cold forest feels as far from you

4
00:00:50,315 --> 00:00:52,886
- [Man] As I could be but knowing you'll be seeing

5
00:00:52,922 --> 00:00:55,355
the same moon in just a few hours,

6
00:00:55,390 --> 00:00:57,023
the world seems small again.

7
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,699
I have some incredible news,

8
00:00:59,733 --> 00:01:02,410
by the time you receive this I'll be somewhere mid Atlantic

9
00:01:02,444 --> 00:01:05,121
steaming towards you at 20 knots.

10
00:01:05,156 --> 00:01:07,692
I wanna marry you the minute I'm home.

11
00:01:07,728 --> 00:01:11,585
- [Both] Until then I'm jealous of the moon.

12
00:01:11,620 --> 00:01:12,733
- Mary! Mary!

13
00:01:16,834 --> 00:01:18,294
He's coming home!

14
00:01:18,330 --> 00:01:19,754
Hank's coming home!

15
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:22,395
(gentle music)

16
00:01:38,522 --> 00:01:40,573
Mom those are your good pearls.

17
00:01:40,608 --> 00:01:42,276
- Oh they're perfect for the bodice.

18
00:01:42,312 --> 00:01:43,180
Now one more time,

19
00:01:43,215 --> 00:01:44,988
- We've already done this.

20
00:01:45,022 --> 00:01:46,482
- Measure twice, cut once.

21
00:01:46,516 --> 00:01:49,297
(gentle music)

22
00:02:35,872 --> 00:02:38,340
Okay, now don't open them until I tell you.

23
00:02:43,935 --> 00:02:44,838
Woody.

24
00:02:45,951 --> 00:02:48,349
- What do you think Daddy?

25
00:02:49,565 --> 00:02:50,469
- Excuse me.

26
00:02:52,173 --> 00:02:53,562
- Daddy?

27
00:02:53,598 --> 00:02:55,683
- Let him go, he'll be fine.

28
00:02:55,718 --> 00:02:58,429
(engine rumbles)

29
00:02:59,576 --> 00:03:00,966
- Oh my God it's Hank.

30
00:03:06,597 --> 00:03:07,465
Hank!

31
00:03:09,864 --> 00:03:11,636
- Captain Jeffries ma'am.

32
00:03:11,671 --> 00:03:13,617
Are you Hannah Pinkum?

33
00:03:18,241 --> 00:03:20,221
- Mary get your father.

34
00:03:20,257 --> 00:03:23,211
(dramatic music)

35
00:03:30,822 --> 00:03:35,479
(tearing) (crying)

36
00:03:40,658 --> 00:03:43,578
(dramatic music)

37
00:03:55,812 --> 00:03:58,002
- I wanna read something that I wrote for Hank.

38
00:03:58,037 --> 00:03:59,393
- [Mary] Okay.

39
00:04:03,772 --> 00:04:07,004
- Before you I never dreamed that stars could rise

40
00:04:07,039 --> 00:04:09,889
under my feet, that eyes could sing,

41
00:04:11,245 --> 00:04:14,964
that we could go quietly about flinging open windows

42
00:04:14,998 --> 00:04:17,084
though death itself had locked the door.

43
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:24,452
One day may this dress be worn by someone

44
00:04:24,486 --> 00:04:27,441
who's found the kind of love where nothing is impossible.

45
00:04:27,476 --> 00:04:30,083
(gentle music)

46
00:04:40,997 --> 00:04:43,429
(clattering)

47
00:04:44,890 --> 00:04:47,948
- Iris, oh there's my girl.

48
00:04:47,982 --> 00:04:50,034
Hello, hi gorgeous.

49
00:04:50,068 --> 00:04:52,431
Come on, help me get this all set up okay?

50
00:04:54,586 --> 00:04:55,977
Want some water?

51
00:04:56,012 --> 00:04:58,723
Travis, yes Travis is coming.

52
00:05:00,913 --> 00:05:02,476
Come on we don't have much time.

53
00:05:04,145 --> 00:05:08,732
Okay Iris no wagging, no slurping, and no being a dog.

54
00:05:10,609 --> 00:05:13,599
Oh Iris, how do I look?

55
00:05:13,633 --> 00:05:15,997
(footsteps)

56
00:05:20,238 --> 00:05:21,211
- Where is she?

57
00:05:21,245 --> 00:05:23,192
Where is my girl?

58
00:05:23,227 --> 00:05:26,042
Hey sweetheart, come here.

59
00:05:28,023 --> 00:05:31,012
You got fat, you got bathed.

60
00:05:31,047 --> 00:05:32,472
You didn't miss me at all.

61
00:05:32,506 --> 00:05:33,376
Hey you.

62
00:05:33,410 --> 00:05:34,314
- Hey.

63
00:05:35,739 --> 00:05:36,643
Hi.

64
00:05:38,346 --> 00:05:39,875
- The place looks incredible.

65
00:05:39,910 --> 00:05:41,092
- You know me, I'm a fixer.

66
00:05:42,725 --> 00:05:46,340
- Zoey, Zoey do I wish you had been with me in New York.

67
00:05:47,730 --> 00:05:49,294
You know me and organization.

68
00:05:49,329 --> 00:05:53,048
You are my right hand, my left brain,

69
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:56,177
my north pole and my south paw.

70
00:05:57,844 --> 00:06:00,729
- So besides being miserable without me

71
00:06:00,764 --> 00:06:03,892
did you manage to have fun and get famous?

72
00:06:03,926 --> 00:06:06,568
- Got a show at the Bierman Gallery this June

73
00:06:06,603 --> 00:06:10,392
and photographs by Travis Cleveland at the Sinclair Studio

74
00:06:10,426 --> 00:06:11,643
in September.

75
00:06:12,928 --> 00:06:13,554
- Are you serious?

76
00:06:13,588 --> 00:06:14,736
- Yeah!

77
00:06:14,771 --> 00:06:17,239
- So does this mean I should save your grocery lists

78
00:06:17,273 --> 00:06:18,733
and make you sign my t-shirts?

79
00:06:18,768 --> 00:06:21,376
- Zoey you're not gonna believe this,

80
00:06:21,409 --> 00:06:24,676
I met the woman of my dreams.

81
00:06:27,491 --> 00:06:29,890
You never thought I'd get married did ya?

82
00:06:29,925 --> 00:06:30,933
- No, no I did.

83
00:06:30,968 --> 00:06:32,949
- [Travis] Well you're right.

84
00:06:32,984 --> 00:06:35,764
It was fate, I met her at the Wheeler opening,

85
00:06:35,799 --> 00:06:36,738
she's one of his models.

86
00:06:36,772 --> 00:06:37,815
- A model.

87
00:06:37,849 --> 00:06:39,900
- Yeah, yeah but I really think you'll like her.

88
00:06:39,935 --> 00:06:41,603
She's smart and she's sensitive

89
00:06:41,637 --> 00:06:42,576
and funny and--

90
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:44,453
- And beautiful.

91
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:45,392
- I'm a goner.

92
00:06:46,747 --> 00:06:49,875
Oh hey would you get us a couple cappuccinos.

93
00:06:49,911 --> 00:06:51,439
Cass should be here any minute.

94
00:06:51,474 --> 00:06:54,012
And Cass said that she likes hers with extra foam.

95
00:06:55,575 --> 00:06:57,349
(tapping)

96
00:06:57,383 --> 00:06:58,183
- Hey.

97
00:06:58,217 --> 00:06:59,364
- [Vendor] Hey.

98
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:02,284
- One with sugar, one without and one with extra foam.

99
00:07:02,318 --> 00:07:03,327
- [Vendor] You got it.

100
00:07:03,361 --> 00:07:04,335
- And ground glass.

101
00:07:09,861 --> 00:07:12,468
(door bangs)

102
00:07:15,978 --> 00:07:18,758
- Red hot cappuccinos for the red hot lovers.

103
00:07:19,871 --> 00:07:21,713
- Cass come meet Zoey.

104
00:07:21,747 --> 00:07:25,224
Zoey I want you to meet my bride to be.

105
00:07:25,258 --> 00:07:26,371
Thanks.

106
00:07:26,405 --> 00:07:27,275
- Hi.

107
00:07:27,309 --> 00:07:28,178
- Hi.

108
00:07:28,213 --> 00:07:29,012
(dog barks)

109
00:07:29,046 --> 00:07:29,638
- Iris, Iris.

110
00:07:29,672 --> 00:07:30,576
What's gotten into you.

111
00:07:30,610 --> 00:07:32,522
- Cass I recognize you from magazines.

112
00:07:32,556 --> 00:07:33,739
- Oh which magazine?

113
00:07:33,773 --> 00:07:38,708
- Ah let's see maybe Biker Mama's or Roughage and You.

114
00:07:38,744 --> 00:07:40,447
(laughs)

115
00:07:40,481 --> 00:07:43,435
- She's funny Travis, no wonder you like her.

116
00:07:43,471 --> 00:07:46,877
- I'm nothing without Zoey, I'm nuts and she's the bolts.

117
00:07:46,912 --> 00:07:48,024
(growls)

118
00:07:48,059 --> 00:07:50,040
Iris stop that!

119
00:07:50,074 --> 00:07:51,187
- Is that your dog Zoey.

120
00:07:51,221 --> 00:07:52,091
- No she's mine.

121
00:07:52,126 --> 00:07:54,453
Whenever I'm out of town like this she,

122
00:07:54,488 --> 00:07:57,305
you know, wants my undivided attention.

123
00:07:57,339 --> 00:07:58,590
- Well who can blame her?

124
00:08:00,328 --> 00:08:01,197
(growls) (barks)

125
00:08:01,232 --> 00:08:02,205
- Iris stop!

126
00:08:03,873 --> 00:08:04,776
- Yikes.

127
00:08:06,653 --> 00:08:08,460
So Zoey do you have a boyfriend?

128
00:08:08,496 --> 00:08:12,180
- Ah, yeah until recently.

129
00:08:12,215 --> 00:08:14,787
- Oh well maybe you'll meet someone at our wedding.

130
00:08:14,821 --> 00:08:16,420
Wouldn't that be perfect?

131
00:08:16,455 --> 00:08:21,529
Travis look, this was my absolute dream dress.

132
00:08:22,572 --> 00:08:24,553
And it costs an absolute fortune.

133
00:08:26,534 --> 00:08:28,342
- Yeah, it's interesting.

134
00:08:29,837 --> 00:08:30,948
What do you think Zoey?

135
00:08:36,788 --> 00:08:40,959
- It kinda looks like a futuristic nurse uniform.

136
00:08:40,993 --> 00:08:41,897
- Excuse me?

137
00:08:43,079 --> 00:08:45,025
Do you realize who designed this dress?

138
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:46,034
Wilhelmina Pringle.

139
00:08:48,224 --> 00:08:51,212
- It'd be like us coveting a Hastleblaght Zoe.

140
00:08:51,248 --> 00:08:52,881
Hey we want the best right?

141
00:08:52,915 --> 00:08:55,905
- Well I obviously do, look who I fell in love with.

142
00:08:57,816 --> 00:08:59,657
(barks)

143
00:08:59,693 --> 00:09:00,596
- I'm sorry.

144
00:09:03,828 --> 00:09:04,732
- Yikes.

145
00:09:08,243 --> 00:09:09,598
Goodnight.

146
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:11,163
- Zoey, come here.

147
00:09:13,491 --> 00:09:14,465
What do you think?

148
00:09:20,165 --> 00:09:23,293
- Wow, I'm so impressed.

149
00:09:24,787 --> 00:09:27,186
- I don't believe my ears.

150
00:09:27,221 --> 00:09:29,340
- Don't flatter yourself.

151
00:09:29,376 --> 00:09:31,495
The lighting could be improved.

152
00:09:31,530 --> 00:09:33,476
You should have taken your assistant.

153
00:09:34,553 --> 00:09:36,466
- Oh hey, I wanna show you.

154
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:39,490
Look, this is when I met Cass.

155
00:09:39,524 --> 00:09:43,904
This very shot was my first glimpse of her.

156
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:48,283
I wanted to capture the actual subjects

157
00:09:48,319 --> 00:09:52,141
of Wheeler's posed shots but quickly to--

158
00:09:52,176 --> 00:09:54,887
- Have them as unposed as possible.

159
00:09:54,921 --> 00:09:57,563
Expose the real self observing the social self.

160
00:09:59,336 --> 00:10:01,352
- You know me too well.

161
00:10:01,387 --> 00:10:06,323
- Well I know this much, I know that love is blind

162
00:10:06,357 --> 00:10:08,824
and one of us needs a seeing eye dog.

163
00:10:08,859 --> 00:10:10,562
- Am I that far gone?

164
00:10:10,597 --> 00:10:12,717
(chuckling)

165
00:10:12,751 --> 00:10:15,741
- Travis there's something I have to tell you.

166
00:10:15,775 --> 00:10:17,305
- Look is it about Cass?

167
00:10:17,340 --> 00:10:20,538
Because I know it seems shallow that I picked a beautiful

168
00:10:20,572 --> 00:10:22,623
model, it seems corny

169
00:10:22,658 --> 00:10:25,264
but she's beautiful on the inside too.

170
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,654
- You're right.

171
00:10:26,689 --> 00:10:27,801
- You mean you can see that?

172
00:10:27,837 --> 00:10:30,305
- No, you're right it sounds corny.

173
00:10:30,339 --> 00:10:34,440
- Stop, she she has a degree in social work,

174
00:10:34,475 --> 00:10:36,109
she took care of her grandmother when she was dying

175
00:10:36,143 --> 00:10:37,776
of cancer, she has a good heart.

176
00:10:38,993 --> 00:10:42,261
- All I need to know is that you love her.

177
00:10:42,296 --> 00:10:44,103
- But I want you to like her Zoey.

178
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,570
- Maybe I will in time.

179
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,151
- What did you want to ask me?

180
00:10:50,185 --> 00:10:51,436
(phone ringing)

181
00:10:51,471 --> 00:10:52,341
Sorry.

182
00:10:55,538 --> 00:10:56,823
Hello, Cleveland Studios.

183
00:10:58,006 --> 00:10:59,257
Oh hey honey we're just...

184
00:10:59,292 --> 00:11:01,586
Whoa, whoa, whao, slow down.

185
00:11:02,976 --> 00:11:05,339
Cass do they know that that's not my specialty?

186
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:08,085
Uh huh.

187
00:11:08,121 --> 00:11:09,579
Let me--

188
00:11:09,614 --> 00:11:11,283
(phone clatters)

189
00:11:11,318 --> 00:11:14,342
The photographer from Cass's shoot has pneumonia.

190
00:11:14,377 --> 00:11:16,670
(chatting)

191
00:11:21,466 --> 00:11:22,683
- Cut, cut.

192
00:11:22,718 --> 00:11:24,490
- What sweet heart, tell us what?

193
00:11:24,525 --> 00:11:25,707
- This is not working.

194
00:11:25,741 --> 00:11:27,341
The wind, the smoke, my eyes are tearing,

195
00:11:27,376 --> 00:11:29,252
my makeup's running and there's a bee somewhere

196
00:11:29,287 --> 00:11:30,400
and I'm allergic to bees.

197
00:11:30,433 --> 00:11:32,276
- Maybe we should call in the swat team.

198
00:11:32,311 --> 00:11:33,492
- Zoey, turn the fan off.

199
00:11:33,527 --> 00:11:34,430
- Yup.

200
00:11:36,204 --> 00:11:37,073
(clatters)

201
00:11:37,107 --> 00:11:38,567
- Whoa, whoa.

202
00:11:38,601 --> 00:11:40,861
What is this the third mistake in the last three minutes?

203
00:11:40,895 --> 00:11:42,564
Who are you, the elephant child?

204
00:11:42,598 --> 00:11:45,901
- Hey she happens to be the best assistant around.

205
00:11:45,935 --> 00:11:48,056
Armond, if you have a problem talk to me.

206
00:11:56,536 --> 00:11:59,004
Don't worry about them we're doing great, okay?

207
00:11:59,039 --> 00:12:02,028
- This is unreal here, doesn't it bother you?

208
00:12:02,063 --> 00:12:03,036
- Hello?

209
00:12:03,071 --> 00:12:05,503
We're ready, does anyone care, can we shoot?

210
00:12:08,806 --> 00:12:10,370
- [Zoey] Hey Travis.

211
00:12:10,405 --> 00:12:12,177
- Hey good morning, how'd those prints turn out?

212
00:12:12,212 --> 00:12:13,706
Armond needs them by three.

213
00:12:13,741 --> 00:12:16,244
- Well the locomotive looks great.

214
00:12:18,155 --> 00:12:20,380
Oh something big came for you, I think it's from your aunt.

215
00:12:20,414 --> 00:12:23,577
- Oh cool, could you open it for me while I check these out?

216
00:12:23,612 --> 00:12:24,515
Elephant child.

217
00:12:43,354 --> 00:12:45,439
Hey don't you want to hear this?

218
00:12:45,474 --> 00:12:46,864
- Are you kidding of course I do,

219
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:49,402
I was just pretending to respect your privacy.

220
00:12:50,409 --> 00:12:51,314
- Oh look.

221
00:12:55,484 --> 00:12:56,492
My darling nephew,

222
00:12:57,743 --> 00:13:00,385
I was so happy to hear you found your soul mate

223
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:03,340
and I can't wait to meet her.

224
00:13:03,374 --> 00:13:05,286
- I remember how fascinated you were

225
00:13:05,321 --> 00:13:07,962
with the story of this dress.

226
00:13:07,997 --> 00:13:10,568
It wasn't my destiny to wear it

227
00:13:10,603 --> 00:13:13,210
but perhaps it could be your brides.

228
00:13:14,149 --> 00:13:16,582
I past the dress onto you now,

229
00:13:16,616 --> 00:13:19,501
in hopes that she will love it as much as I did.

230
00:13:19,536 --> 00:13:22,282
(gentle music)

231
00:13:30,206 --> 00:13:34,586
- This is the most beautiful wedding dress I have ever seen.

232
00:13:35,907 --> 00:13:37,504
- Well I'm sure it's a beautiful dress

233
00:13:37,540 --> 00:13:39,139
but can't I just think about it?

234
00:13:39,174 --> 00:13:40,807
My hearts so set on the Wilhelmina Pringle.

235
00:13:40,842 --> 00:13:43,831
- Yeah Cass, we can't afford that dress.

236
00:13:43,866 --> 00:13:44,943
- Daddy says he'll get it for me.

237
00:13:46,576 --> 00:13:49,496
- Look let's just wait until you see aunt Hannah's.

238
00:13:49,530 --> 00:13:50,539
I think that you're gonna love it

239
00:13:50,573 --> 00:13:53,007
and if you don't then I totally understand.

240
00:13:54,988 --> 00:13:55,857
- Okay.

241
00:13:55,891 --> 00:13:56,761
- Yeah?

242
00:13:56,795 --> 00:13:57,490
- Mmhmm.

243
00:14:00,132 --> 00:14:03,678
- So Armond didn't I tell you that he was a genius?

244
00:14:03,712 --> 00:14:04,755
- Obviously.

245
00:14:06,736 --> 00:14:09,656
I can't use these.

246
00:14:09,690 --> 00:14:12,020
They're far to, well they're to real.

247
00:14:13,478 --> 00:14:16,955
Women don't buy the cloth, they buy the image.

248
00:14:16,989 --> 00:14:20,743
The shot has to say fun, sex, danger,

249
00:14:20,778 --> 00:14:22,377
catch me, play with me.

250
00:14:22,411 --> 00:14:25,922
These say stiff girl standing on a train.

251
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:30,718
- Cass told me you wanted real.

252
00:14:30,753 --> 00:14:33,951
- Well Travis I didn't mean this real.

253
00:14:36,002 --> 00:14:38,156
- They let you look natural and ravishing.

254
00:14:38,192 --> 00:14:40,068
Isn't that anyone's fantasy?

255
00:14:40,103 --> 00:14:42,153
- Don't worry I'll get you another chance.

256
00:14:42,188 --> 00:14:43,821
Armond's not the only coordinator in the business.

257
00:14:43,856 --> 00:14:45,733
- It's not my thing Cass.

258
00:14:45,768 --> 00:14:47,298
I'm happier doing the work I do.

259
00:14:47,332 --> 00:14:49,001
- Yeah but it's limiting financially.

260
00:14:49,035 --> 00:14:51,746
I mean, why not broaden your options?

261
00:14:52,824 --> 00:14:54,179
- I make a fine living.

262
00:14:57,273 --> 00:15:00,991
- Travis, oh my God, I'm so sorry I couldn't resist,

263
00:15:01,027 --> 00:15:02,520
please forgive me.

264
00:15:02,556 --> 00:15:05,198
- Nah it's okay Zoey, really it's okay.

265
00:15:05,232 --> 00:15:08,951
Wow you look, you really look,

266
00:15:10,063 --> 00:15:12,288
uh that dress, that dress is amazing.

267
00:15:13,643 --> 00:15:15,033
- Yes it is, isn't it?

268
00:15:16,493 --> 00:15:21,567
I see what you meant Travis it's totally one of a kind.

269
00:15:22,818 --> 00:15:25,738
- Travis I'm so embarrassed I had no right.

270
00:15:25,774 --> 00:15:27,545
- Well I can't wait to try it on.

271
00:15:27,581 --> 00:15:29,075
How about right now?

272
00:15:29,110 --> 00:15:30,013
- Why not?

273
00:15:31,126 --> 00:15:31,995
I'll just...

274
00:15:32,030 --> 00:15:33,316
Iris let's go for a walk.

275
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:37,348
(barks)

276
00:15:38,598 --> 00:15:41,379
- So how long have you been in love with him?

277
00:15:41,414 --> 00:15:43,186
- I can't remember when I wasn't.

278
00:15:45,793 --> 00:15:46,940
I've written him a goodbye letter.

279
00:15:46,975 --> 00:15:49,339
Could you give it to him for me?

280
00:15:49,374 --> 00:15:50,139
- You're leaving?

281
00:15:50,173 --> 00:15:51,841
- Tomorrow morning.

282
00:15:51,876 --> 00:15:52,884
- Oh.

283
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:55,594
Well I'll have to hire him a male assistant.

284
00:15:55,630 --> 00:15:57,020
Any woman would fall in love with him.

285
00:15:58,341 --> 00:16:01,017
- He gets more amazing the longer you've known him.

286
00:16:04,041 --> 00:16:06,647
- God this looks like a lampshade in a whorehouse.

287
00:16:06,682 --> 00:16:11,271
- Cass, you have no idea how much this dress means to Travis

288
00:16:11,305 --> 00:16:14,399
and his family, pretend to like it.

289
00:16:14,433 --> 00:16:15,164
It's crucial.

290
00:16:16,102 --> 00:16:17,839
- So why are you helping me out?

291
00:16:19,821 --> 00:16:22,149
- All the years I've known him,

292
00:16:22,184 --> 00:16:23,817
he's never been like this.

293
00:16:27,258 --> 00:16:28,301
He really loves you.

294
00:16:30,213 --> 00:16:31,117
Be good to him.

295
00:16:37,025 --> 00:16:39,666
(door thuds)

296
00:16:56,142 --> 00:16:58,366
(door creaks)

297
00:16:58,401 --> 00:17:00,486
- Hey, oh I missed you in the dress.

298
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:02,884
- I'm so late to my parents, it's already three.

299
00:17:02,919 --> 00:17:04,517
I loved it though.

300
00:17:04,553 --> 00:17:05,908
- Okay, good, well I'll bring it with me

301
00:17:05,943 --> 00:17:07,125
so they can see it too.

302
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:08,064
Where's Zoey?

303
00:17:10,288 --> 00:17:15,500
- Ah, honey, I hate to tell you on the run like this,

304
00:17:17,030 --> 00:17:19,741
but she said to tell you that she quit.

305
00:17:19,776 --> 00:17:20,680
She just left.

306
00:17:22,904 --> 00:17:23,842
- Are you serious?

307
00:17:26,102 --> 00:17:27,006
Did she say why?

308
00:17:27,041 --> 00:17:30,169
- Nothing, she was totally embarrassed.

309
00:17:30,203 --> 00:17:33,263
Maybe she just realized it was a dead end job.

310
00:17:33,297 --> 00:17:36,217
Anyway she said to tell you she's sorry.

311
00:17:36,251 --> 00:17:38,510
Travis forgive me, I have to go.

312
00:17:38,544 --> 00:17:40,109
- Yeah go, go.

313
00:17:40,144 --> 00:17:42,195
I'll see you at five.

314
00:17:42,229 --> 00:17:43,098
- Okay.

315
00:17:43,133 --> 00:17:44,036
- Bye.

316
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,833
(door thuds)

317
00:17:51,162 --> 00:17:54,081
(engine rumbles)

318
00:18:01,554 --> 00:18:04,543
(door bell rings)

319
00:18:06,523 --> 00:18:07,706
- [Woman] I think it looks good.

320
00:18:07,740 --> 00:18:08,853
- [Woman] Yeah I think it's right.

321
00:18:08,887 --> 00:18:09,930
- [Woman] Yeah.

322
00:18:09,966 --> 00:18:12,815
- Travis is here with his aunt's wedding dress.

323
00:18:12,850 --> 00:18:15,526
- Mom you've got to stall him.

324
00:18:15,561 --> 00:18:17,091
- I'll introduce him to grandma.

325
00:18:18,759 --> 00:18:21,678
- We didn't think she'd ever find Mr. Right.

326
00:18:21,713 --> 00:18:22,616
She's too picky.

327
00:18:23,799 --> 00:18:25,189
- Well I'm glad she picked me.

328
00:18:25,224 --> 00:18:26,231
(chuckles)

329
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:28,630
- I married the first man who winked at me.

330
00:18:28,664 --> 00:18:31,444
Just think I might've married some nitwit

331
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:32,801
with dust in his eyes.

332
00:18:32,835 --> 00:18:33,704
(laughing)

333
00:18:33,739 --> 00:18:37,805
But fate was kind, I got me a plumb.

334
00:18:39,717 --> 00:18:42,011
But, he's gone now.

335
00:18:43,297 --> 00:18:45,870
I lost Mr. Hotchkiss to cancer two years ago.

336
00:18:45,904 --> 00:18:48,406
- Yeah Cass told me how close you and she became

337
00:18:48,441 --> 00:18:51,118
when she nursed you through your illness.

338
00:18:52,438 --> 00:18:55,393
- I've been in perfect health all of my life.

339
00:18:55,427 --> 00:18:57,860
- Oh I'm sorry maybe ah, maybe she was talking about

340
00:18:57,895 --> 00:18:59,181
her other grandmother.

341
00:19:00,536 --> 00:19:03,421
- She died before Cass was born.

342
00:19:03,456 --> 00:19:06,168
- Cass said this was when she was getting her degree

343
00:19:06,202 --> 00:19:08,079
in social work at UCLA.

344
00:19:08,114 --> 00:19:10,616
- Wouldn't that be something if they gave degrees

345
00:19:10,651 --> 00:19:12,215
in socializing?

346
00:19:12,250 --> 00:19:15,204
- But she did go to UCLA didn't she?

347
00:19:16,177 --> 00:19:18,610
- Oh Travis, forgive me

348
00:19:18,644 --> 00:19:23,094
but these are things you need to discuss with your bride.

349
00:19:23,129 --> 00:19:25,179
(doors clattering)

350
00:19:25,215 --> 00:19:25,944
- Travis.

351
00:19:29,489 --> 00:19:31,158
- I think you owe me an explanation.

352
00:19:31,193 --> 00:19:32,896
- And why is that?

353
00:19:32,930 --> 00:19:35,710
I don't tell you how to take your photographs do I?

354
00:19:35,746 --> 00:19:38,388
That's your territory and I respect that.

355
00:19:38,421 --> 00:19:40,577
- Yeah but this isn't just about a dress Cass.

356
00:19:40,611 --> 00:19:42,106
This is about what we mean to each other,

357
00:19:42,141 --> 00:19:43,948
this is about trust.

358
00:19:43,983 --> 00:19:46,103
Why would you lie about UCLA?

359
00:19:46,138 --> 00:19:49,266
- I didn't lie, I took some extension classes.

360
00:19:49,301 --> 00:19:51,907
- Why would you tell me grandmother had cancer?

361
00:19:51,943 --> 00:19:53,889
- So it was a friend's grandmother?

362
00:19:54,931 --> 00:19:56,774
- And what was that with Armond?

363
00:19:56,808 --> 00:19:59,068
You sold me down the river without a second thought.

364
00:19:59,102 --> 00:20:01,639
- I got you that opportunity and you blew it.

365
00:20:04,142 --> 00:20:05,915
- And you never had any intention of wearing the dress

366
00:20:05,949 --> 00:20:07,096
did you?

367
00:20:07,131 --> 00:20:10,120
- Well Travis, you're supposed to eat a wedding cake

368
00:20:10,155 --> 00:20:11,267
not wear it.

369
00:20:13,630 --> 00:20:14,500
- Wow.

370
00:20:14,534 --> 00:20:15,890
- This is my wedding day

371
00:20:17,141 --> 00:20:19,504
and if I can't make my own fashion statement

372
00:20:19,539 --> 00:20:21,069
on this day of all days,

373
00:20:21,103 --> 00:20:23,293
then guess who's not being respected?

374
00:20:24,683 --> 00:20:25,726
- You're absolutely right Cass

375
00:20:27,117 --> 00:20:29,618
and I don't think I can marry someone I don't respect.

376
00:20:29,653 --> 00:20:32,573
(dramatic music)

377
00:20:41,679 --> 00:20:43,417
(jingles)

378
00:20:43,452 --> 00:20:45,467
(dramatic music)

379
00:20:45,503 --> 00:20:47,935
(door bangs)

380
00:20:52,419 --> 00:20:53,427
(clatters)

381
00:20:53,462 --> 00:20:55,408
Iris, what's gotten into you?

382
00:20:55,442 --> 00:20:58,363
(dramatic music)

383
00:21:06,392 --> 00:21:08,165
- [Zoey Voiceover] How I've loved being your right hand,

384
00:21:08,199 --> 00:21:12,126
your left brain, your north pole and your south paw.

385
00:21:12,162 --> 00:21:14,942
It's sad that even with all those directions

386
00:21:14,977 --> 00:21:17,271
I still couldn't find my way into your heart.

387
00:21:18,279 --> 00:21:19,981
I'll always love you, Zoey.

388
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:25,647
(clattering)

389
00:21:29,575 --> 00:21:32,182
- [Phone] The number you have reached has been disconnected

390
00:21:32,216 --> 00:21:33,710
and there is no new number.

391
00:21:33,746 --> 00:21:34,857
(clatters)

392
00:21:34,893 --> 00:21:37,811
(dramatic music)

393
00:21:49,559 --> 00:21:51,403
(clicking)

394
00:21:51,436 --> 00:21:54,704
(light hearted music)

395
00:21:59,918 --> 00:22:03,359
- 1,600 hours of school, then I get a license

396
00:22:03,393 --> 00:22:04,644
and I can cut hair.

397
00:22:04,679 --> 00:22:08,294
Like my uncle said a little hard work never killed anyone.

398
00:22:08,329 --> 00:22:10,483
- Yeah but why take the chance.

399
00:22:10,517 --> 00:22:12,257
- Not one nickel Billy.

400
00:22:12,291 --> 00:22:14,620
- Aw come on Lula I'm not here for money.

401
00:22:14,654 --> 00:22:15,523
- Of course not.

402
00:22:15,558 --> 00:22:17,018
Where would I get that idea?

403
00:22:17,052 --> 00:22:19,520
- Let me take you to lunch then.

404
00:22:19,555 --> 00:22:20,562
- I'm on a diet.

405
00:22:20,598 --> 00:22:23,100
- Well okay, well marry me then.

406
00:22:23,969 --> 00:22:25,082
Hey come on.

407
00:22:25,116 --> 00:22:27,167
- Oh sure so we can live in your mother's kitchen,

408
00:22:27,201 --> 00:22:29,843
sleep all day, scam all night.

409
00:22:29,878 --> 00:22:32,484
Oh and then we can have kids and you can grow up with them.

410
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:33,910
- Lula.

411
00:22:33,945 --> 00:22:36,621
- Marriage is work, responsibility,

412
00:22:36,655 --> 00:22:39,123
something you know nothing about.

413
00:22:39,159 --> 00:22:41,904
You treat marriage like it's silly

414
00:22:41,939 --> 00:22:43,990
and marriage is serious.

415
00:22:44,024 --> 00:22:46,700
- But I am serious Lula.

416
00:22:46,735 --> 00:22:49,724
I need you in a serious, serious way.

417
00:22:49,758 --> 00:22:51,740
- Then do three things for me Billy.

418
00:22:51,775 --> 00:22:56,989
Get a car, a job and propose to me so sweet my knees quiver.

419
00:22:58,726 --> 00:23:01,750
- Well I think I have the first one covered.

420
00:23:08,389 --> 00:23:11,031
- Billy, where did you get this?

421
00:23:12,143 --> 00:23:14,297
- That's not all I got Lula, look I...

422
00:23:16,696 --> 00:23:17,982
I got a camera too.

423
00:23:19,024 --> 00:23:20,414
- You know what you're gonna get?

424
00:23:20,449 --> 00:23:24,378
You're gonna get a rap sheet a mile long.

425
00:23:24,411 --> 00:23:26,324
You stole this whole rig didn't you?

426
00:23:27,644 --> 00:23:29,903
- Come on Lula all I wanna steal is your heart.

427
00:23:31,432 --> 00:23:35,986
- Prove to me you're responsible and then we'll talk.

428
00:23:36,020 --> 00:23:39,323
(light hearted music)

429
00:23:43,562 --> 00:23:46,482
(engine rumbles)

430
00:23:49,853 --> 00:23:52,495
(vocalizing)

431
00:23:57,500 --> 00:24:00,420
(engine rumbles)

432
00:24:14,461 --> 00:24:18,424
(tires squealing) (light hearted music)

433
00:24:18,458 --> 00:24:21,344
(crying out)

434
00:24:21,379 --> 00:24:26,592
(tires squealing) (light hearted music)

435
00:24:31,007 --> 00:24:33,092
(bangs)

436
00:24:37,228 --> 00:24:38,236
- Hey! Hey you!

437
00:24:38,270 --> 00:24:39,174
Hey! Hey!

438
00:24:40,252 --> 00:24:42,406
Hey, hey are you alright?

439
00:24:45,013 --> 00:24:45,951
Where the hell you going?

440
00:24:45,987 --> 00:24:47,933
What about your car...

441
00:24:49,531 --> 00:24:52,138
(gentle music)

442
00:25:03,747 --> 00:25:06,527
(upbeat music)

443
00:25:12,123 --> 00:25:14,244
Oh Laura, Laura you work too hard.

444
00:25:14,279 --> 00:25:15,912
- I don't what you're looking at that menu for

445
00:25:15,947 --> 00:25:17,059
you know you're gonna have your regular.

446
00:25:17,094 --> 00:25:18,831
- I'm trying to turn over a new leaf here,

447
00:25:18,866 --> 00:25:22,030
do something different, give my life some new life.

448
00:25:22,064 --> 00:25:23,177
- Oh that would be nice.

449
00:25:23,211 --> 00:25:26,235
- So, I'll have a coconut donut.

450
00:25:26,270 --> 00:25:27,555
That's healthy right?

451
00:25:27,590 --> 00:25:28,702
(laughing)

452
00:25:28,738 --> 00:25:30,440
Hey, how's Paul doing?

453
00:25:31,483 --> 00:25:33,291
- I hardly ever see him.

454
00:25:33,326 --> 00:25:34,611
When he's not at the hospital

455
00:25:34,646 --> 00:25:36,697
he's at the library studying.

456
00:25:36,731 --> 00:25:38,643
- Well it's all gonna be worth it.

457
00:25:38,677 --> 00:25:41,041
I even got you an early wedding present.

458
00:25:42,779 --> 00:25:44,101
- Art.

459
00:25:44,135 --> 00:25:46,151
- Anybody see a dress in there?

460
00:25:46,186 --> 00:25:47,575
- Yeah no, it's a wedding dress.

461
00:25:47,610 --> 00:25:48,653
The camera I don't care about

462
00:25:48,688 --> 00:25:50,773
but the dress it's irreplaceable.

463
00:25:50,808 --> 00:25:52,650
- [Man] No, there's no dress in here.

464
00:25:52,684 --> 00:25:53,589
- God.

465
00:25:53,623 --> 00:25:55,292
- [Man] I didn't see any dress in there.

466
00:25:55,327 --> 00:25:56,647
- Hey is there anything you guys could do?

467
00:25:56,681 --> 00:25:57,655
Hey! Could you...

468
00:25:57,690 --> 00:25:59,601
Could you put out an APB on it?

469
00:26:03,564 --> 00:26:06,310
(dramatic music)

470
00:26:12,044 --> 00:26:13,469
- Oh my God.

471
00:26:13,504 --> 00:26:15,728
Art where did you get this?

472
00:26:15,764 --> 00:26:17,049
- It was a gift.

473
00:26:18,196 --> 00:26:20,595
- Somebody gave you a wedding dress?

474
00:26:20,629 --> 00:26:21,811
- Exactly.

475
00:26:21,846 --> 00:26:23,932
(gasps)

476
00:26:23,966 --> 00:26:25,530
Could use a good home huh?

477
00:26:25,565 --> 00:26:27,650
So, what do you think?

478
00:26:27,685 --> 00:26:30,048
- I've never seen anything so beautiful.

479
00:26:31,438 --> 00:26:33,802
You'd need a country club or a fancy hotel

480
00:26:33,837 --> 00:26:35,124
for something like this.

481
00:26:35,158 --> 00:26:38,633
- All you need is what you got.

482
00:26:38,668 --> 00:26:40,372
Now let's see what Paul thinks.

483
00:26:43,465 --> 00:26:44,924
(phone clatters)

484
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:46,419
- I certainly hope it wasn't long distance.

485
00:26:46,453 --> 00:26:47,566
- Dr. Weineger.

486
00:26:47,601 --> 00:26:50,138
No, no, no I was just trying to call my future bride.

487
00:26:50,174 --> 00:26:54,066
We haven't seen each other since Sunday, I think.

488
00:26:54,101 --> 00:26:55,421
What day is it today?

489
00:26:55,455 --> 00:26:58,306
- Believe it or not, it was worse in my day.

490
00:26:58,341 --> 00:27:00,357
I remember my very first surgery.

491
00:27:00,392 --> 00:27:03,589
The procedure went perfectly but when it came time to sign

492
00:27:03,624 --> 00:27:06,474
the report I couldn't even remember my own initials.

493
00:27:06,508 --> 00:27:07,481
So how's Laura?

494
00:27:07,517 --> 00:27:09,706
- Working too hard, sacrificing too much.

495
00:27:09,741 --> 00:27:11,688
You know she deserves a special wedding

496
00:27:11,722 --> 00:27:14,955
but I'm afraid it's gonna be a paper bag lunch

497
00:27:14,989 --> 00:27:17,075
and a crackerjack ring.

498
00:27:17,110 --> 00:27:20,377
- Paul you are a billionaire where it counts.

499
00:27:20,411 --> 00:27:22,011
You invite me to the wedding.

500
00:27:31,603 --> 00:27:32,959
- [Laura] Don't come in here.

501
00:27:32,993 --> 00:27:34,350
- I need my bed.

502
00:27:35,670 --> 00:27:37,512
- [Laura] Honey please get a second wind tonight.

503
00:27:37,546 --> 00:27:39,806
I had such a wonderful day.

504
00:27:39,841 --> 00:27:41,057
- Good tips?

505
00:27:41,092 --> 00:27:42,691
- [Laura] I phoned the electric company,

506
00:27:42,725 --> 00:27:43,942
we got an extension.

507
00:27:43,977 --> 00:27:47,800
- Yeah, well if your getting amorous in there, forget it.

508
00:27:59,027 --> 00:28:01,807
(gentle music)

509
00:28:19,464 --> 00:28:21,272
- It's much to extravagant.

510
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:25,929
I mean we'd have to rent the Four Seasons to go with it but,

511
00:28:27,492 --> 00:28:28,639
isn't it beautiful?

512
00:28:29,787 --> 00:28:32,115
Art gave it to me can you believe it?

513
00:28:34,097 --> 00:28:35,973
It needs a little fixing but...

514
00:28:37,329 --> 00:28:40,665
Look it even fits perfectly.

515
00:28:46,297 --> 00:28:48,243
May I have this dance?

516
00:28:49,945 --> 00:28:51,927
- I was wondering when this would happen.

517
00:28:54,707 --> 00:28:58,113
I am now officially hallucinating.

518
00:28:58,149 --> 00:29:00,929
(gentle music)

519
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:40,378
- I'll find a home for it today.

520
00:29:40,413 --> 00:29:41,768
- Now don't you dare.

521
00:29:42,671 --> 00:29:43,610
We're keeping it.

522
00:29:46,322 --> 00:29:47,399
- Gotta be practical.

523
00:29:49,519 --> 00:29:51,013
- I'll never understand you.

524
00:29:52,091 --> 00:29:53,933
- That's love sickness that's all.

525
00:29:55,462 --> 00:29:56,367
And doctor,

526
00:29:58,834 --> 00:29:59,911
there ain't no cure.

527
00:30:04,916 --> 00:30:08,184
(light hearted music)

528
00:30:29,489 --> 00:30:32,305
- 2,000, this is very short notice,

529
00:30:32,340 --> 00:30:35,189
we'll need 1,000 in advance by tomorrow,

530
00:30:35,225 --> 00:30:37,796
cash, nonrefundable.

531
00:30:37,831 --> 00:30:38,735
- 2,000?

532
00:30:40,369 --> 00:30:42,453
We're on a very tight budget.

533
00:30:42,488 --> 00:30:43,254
- Up to you.

534
00:30:44,469 --> 00:30:46,624
Is a wedding something you put a price tag on?

535
00:30:49,405 --> 00:30:51,699
- I'll bring you the cash tomorrow.

536
00:30:51,734 --> 00:30:55,071
- I love Wednesdays!

537
00:30:55,106 --> 00:30:58,546
We're at home at the same time for two whole hours.

538
00:30:59,381 --> 00:31:00,980
Even when we're old and gray,

539
00:31:02,057 --> 00:31:04,247
let's celebrate Wednesdays okay?

540
00:31:04,281 --> 00:31:06,194
- A world full of voluptuous cynical women

541
00:31:06,228 --> 00:31:08,070
and I fall for a skinny romantic.

542
00:31:09,112 --> 00:31:10,086
They're all pink.

543
00:31:11,302 --> 00:31:12,901
You know that's not easy to accomplish,

544
00:31:12,936 --> 00:31:14,292
we should win something.

545
00:31:15,056 --> 00:31:17,037
My tuition was due last week.

546
00:31:17,072 --> 00:31:18,010
- We have it don't we?

547
00:31:18,046 --> 00:31:19,991
- No, we have $200 left.

548
00:31:20,026 --> 00:31:20,895
- What happened?

549
00:31:20,930 --> 00:31:21,764
I made a deposit.

550
00:31:21,798 --> 00:31:24,962
- Books, phone, rents, bus tokens.

551
00:31:24,997 --> 00:31:26,769
Plus your cruises to Bora Bora.

552
00:31:29,515 --> 00:31:30,418
- What can we do?

553
00:31:32,087 --> 00:31:33,407
- Maybe I should put off school

554
00:31:33,442 --> 00:31:35,216
until we have some money set aside.

555
00:31:35,250 --> 00:31:36,500
- Again?

556
00:31:36,536 --> 00:31:38,968
You've waited so long, this is your last year.

557
00:31:40,915 --> 00:31:42,167
Let's just postpone the wedding.

558
00:31:42,201 --> 00:31:43,105
- No.

559
00:31:47,068 --> 00:31:50,092
Everyday in the hospital I see how fragile life is.

560
00:31:51,099 --> 00:31:53,427
I refuse to postpone our dreams.

561
00:31:55,235 --> 00:31:58,155
(dramatic music)

562
00:32:09,693 --> 00:32:10,597
- Mmm, oh.

563
00:32:13,135 --> 00:32:14,490
You know repairs and dry cleaning alone are gonna

564
00:32:14,524 --> 00:32:16,228
cost me a small fortune.

565
00:32:16,264 --> 00:32:19,634
Then I've gotta tag it, mark and inventory it and sell it

566
00:32:19,669 --> 00:32:21,095
fast before it turns yellow.

567
00:32:21,129 --> 00:32:22,623
Want some gum?

568
00:32:22,658 --> 00:32:24,500
- It's a very special dress.

569
00:32:24,535 --> 00:32:25,577
You don't see detail--

570
00:32:25,612 --> 00:32:29,540
- Ss, honey I have got 750 very specials in here

571
00:32:29,574 --> 00:32:32,391
and every one of them has some sort of story to tell.

572
00:32:34,268 --> 00:32:36,839
- How much do you think?

573
00:32:36,874 --> 00:32:39,828
- 600, oh woof, do you know what?

574
00:32:39,863 --> 00:32:41,600
I am too soft hearted for this business.

575
00:32:41,635 --> 00:32:44,520
(dramatic music)

576
00:32:54,044 --> 00:32:57,485
(light hearted music)

577
00:33:03,950 --> 00:33:05,548
- A grand.

578
00:33:05,583 --> 00:33:08,225
- It's worth at least four, it's solid gold.

579
00:33:08,259 --> 00:33:10,136
It was my father's.

580
00:33:10,171 --> 00:33:12,188
- And if I had a buck every time I heard that line

581
00:33:12,222 --> 00:33:13,195
it would buy me Fort Knox.

582
00:33:13,230 --> 00:33:14,377
Take the thousand go lucky.

583
00:33:15,732 --> 00:33:17,922
I'll give you 3,000 if you sell it to me outright.

584
00:33:17,957 --> 00:33:18,860
- No way.

585
00:33:21,015 --> 00:33:22,197
I'll take the thousand.

586
00:33:26,159 --> 00:33:27,480
I'll have the rest for you in a week.

587
00:33:27,514 --> 00:33:29,809
- We'll need the balance by Sunday.

588
00:33:29,843 --> 00:33:31,095
- But that's in three days.

589
00:33:31,130 --> 00:33:31,999
- Yes it is.

590
00:33:37,213 --> 00:33:38,880
- This is less than half his tuition.

591
00:33:38,915 --> 00:33:41,348
I can't over look the late payment penalty again.

592
00:33:41,384 --> 00:33:42,564
- I'll get it.

593
00:33:44,685 --> 00:33:45,311
- [Paul] Hello?

594
00:33:45,345 --> 00:33:46,319
- [Vendor] Is Laura there?

595
00:33:46,353 --> 00:33:48,056
- She's not here, may I ask who's calling?

596
00:33:48,091 --> 00:33:49,169
- [Vendor] This is Lauren at Wedding Belles.

597
00:33:49,203 --> 00:33:51,845
Um your fiancee brought in her dress this morning

598
00:33:51,879 --> 00:33:54,278
but it seems that she forgot to include the veil.

599
00:33:54,313 --> 00:33:55,633
- It didn't have one.

600
00:33:55,667 --> 00:33:57,962
At least I didn't see one.

601
00:33:57,997 --> 00:33:59,491
She having it altered?

602
00:33:59,525 --> 00:34:02,306
- Not unless she wants to buy it back.

603
00:34:02,342 --> 00:34:06,026
This dress is the rarest find of all.

604
00:34:06,060 --> 00:34:08,423
Mint condition, antique.

605
00:34:09,744 --> 00:34:10,891
Now you wanna go up to Velma's

606
00:34:10,926 --> 00:34:14,158
and pay retail for a cheezy design and polyester lace

607
00:34:14,194 --> 00:34:18,086
be my guest but $1,000 for this dress, a bargain.

608
00:34:19,372 --> 00:34:21,249
- Yeah and how much did you give Laura for it?

609
00:34:21,285 --> 00:34:24,239
- Woof, plenty, I am way too generous.

610
00:34:24,273 --> 00:34:25,316
- Well how about renting it?

611
00:34:25,351 --> 00:34:26,776
- We don't rent.

612
00:34:26,810 --> 00:34:28,479
- You could if you wanted to.

613
00:34:28,513 --> 00:34:30,321
- Look Romeo don't get smart okay?

614
00:34:30,355 --> 00:34:32,337
You wanna get up on that balcony

615
00:34:32,372 --> 00:34:34,214
you gotta climb a prickly vine.

616
00:34:34,248 --> 00:34:38,628
I don't make the rules $1,000 no checks, Visa or Mastercard.

617
00:34:39,949 --> 00:34:43,286
Gum however, is complimentary.

618
00:34:44,536 --> 00:34:46,447
- You told me 2,000 more if I sold it outright

619
00:34:46,482 --> 00:34:47,387
instead of taking the loan.

620
00:34:47,420 --> 00:34:49,680
- I must have been in a generous mood.

621
00:34:49,715 --> 00:34:51,349
But if that's what I said.

622
00:34:51,384 --> 00:34:53,399
- No Mr. Rodericks is not here.

623
00:34:53,434 --> 00:34:56,666
This is his fiancee may I ask what this is regarding?

624
00:34:56,701 --> 00:34:59,482
- [Concierge] Yes we show that he's reserved the Parisenne

625
00:34:59,516 --> 00:35:00,803
room here at the St. George,

626
00:35:00,837 --> 00:35:04,904
please remind him that the rest of the money is due Sunday.

627
00:35:04,938 --> 00:35:06,190
- The rest of the money?

628
00:35:06,225 --> 00:35:07,824
- [Concierge] Yes.

629
00:35:07,858 --> 00:35:08,588
- Of course.

630
00:35:09,700 --> 00:35:12,168
(clatters)

631
00:35:17,590 --> 00:35:18,946
Oh no the dress.

632
00:35:18,980 --> 00:35:21,900
(dramatic music)

633
00:35:22,873 --> 00:35:23,951
- [Paul] Hey honey.

634
00:35:23,985 --> 00:35:25,654
- Dr. Rodericks I presume.

635
00:35:25,688 --> 00:35:27,288
How was your day?

636
00:35:27,322 --> 00:35:28,816
- It's a jungle out there.

637
00:35:29,929 --> 00:35:30,832
Hey.

638
00:35:33,509 --> 00:35:36,290
Tomorrows that big dedication of the new wing

639
00:35:36,324 --> 00:35:39,452
but I'm on call til nine.

640
00:35:39,487 --> 00:35:41,537
- I was really looking forward to going.

641
00:35:41,572 --> 00:35:43,554
I never get out in the world without an apron.

642
00:35:43,588 --> 00:35:45,362
- [Paul] Well it was just a cocktail party.

643
00:35:46,542 --> 00:35:47,933
Are you okay?

644
00:35:47,968 --> 00:35:50,019
- Yeah it's just the bills and everything.

645
00:35:54,954 --> 00:35:55,857
- Go without me.

646
00:35:57,040 --> 00:36:01,385
Now, who can we get as an escort

647
00:36:01,418 --> 00:36:03,052
that wouldn't make me jealous?

648
00:36:03,088 --> 00:36:06,389
(light hearted music)

649
00:36:09,864 --> 00:36:11,672
(grunting)

650
00:36:11,707 --> 00:36:12,644
- Oh yeah, oh.

651
00:36:14,175 --> 00:36:15,878
Sold that dress yesterday.

652
00:36:15,912 --> 00:36:17,650
Well sweetheart a beautiful gown like that

653
00:36:17,685 --> 00:36:18,241
gets snatched right up.

654
00:36:19,875 --> 00:36:22,899
Look around, maybe you'll find something you like better.

655
00:36:22,933 --> 00:36:26,200
(light hearted music)

656
00:36:35,932 --> 00:36:37,739
- Oh no, somebody got it.

657
00:36:37,775 --> 00:36:39,686
- Oh Art I'm so sorry.

658
00:36:39,721 --> 00:36:41,320
You gave us such a wonderful gift--

659
00:36:41,355 --> 00:36:42,293
- Don't you worry about me.

660
00:36:42,329 --> 00:36:44,240
I'm more worried about you.

661
00:36:44,274 --> 00:36:47,194
- Paul still thinks I have the dress.

662
00:36:47,228 --> 00:36:49,591
He rented a hotel banquet room for the wedding

663
00:36:49,627 --> 00:36:51,261
just so I could wear it

664
00:36:51,295 --> 00:36:54,805
and I think he pawned his father's watch.

665
00:36:57,446 --> 00:36:59,012
What am I gonna do?

666
00:36:59,046 --> 00:36:59,949
- Here.

667
00:36:59,984 --> 00:37:02,486
Well you could use a good fairy godmother.

668
00:37:03,773 --> 00:37:05,963
(chattering)

669
00:37:05,997 --> 00:37:06,901
Wow.

670
00:37:10,863 --> 00:37:13,227
Nice party especially the guests.

671
00:37:16,423 --> 00:37:17,710
Oh, sorry.

672
00:37:17,745 --> 00:37:18,613
- Oh so sorry.

673
00:37:18,649 --> 00:37:19,656
Laura?

674
00:37:19,691 --> 00:37:20,908
Dr. Weineger.

675
00:37:20,943 --> 00:37:22,611
I haven't seen you since last semester.

676
00:37:22,646 --> 00:37:25,495
- Dr. Weineger it's so good to see you too.

677
00:37:25,530 --> 00:37:27,234
I've been very busy this spring.

678
00:37:27,269 --> 00:37:30,049
- You and Paul both, he's my best student.

679
00:37:30,084 --> 00:37:32,239
So when are you two going to get married?

680
00:37:33,976 --> 00:37:34,880
- Excuse me.

681
00:37:36,966 --> 00:37:38,008
- Oh boy.

682
00:37:38,043 --> 00:37:39,225
Me and my big mouth.

683
00:37:39,260 --> 00:37:42,561
- Yeah but you have an arm like a Cadillac leaf spring.

684
00:37:42,596 --> 00:37:43,465
- I'm sorry do we--

685
00:37:43,500 --> 00:37:44,716
- Art the Dart Panner.

686
00:37:44,751 --> 00:37:48,053
Marshall High, class of '63, running back.

687
00:37:48,088 --> 00:37:48,956
- Panner?

688
00:37:48,992 --> 00:37:51,633
Oh you old rat, I didn't recognize you.

689
00:37:51,667 --> 00:37:53,614
How do you know Laura?

690
00:37:53,649 --> 00:37:57,507
- Oh well Laura and Paul are like my own kids, you know.

691
00:37:57,541 --> 00:38:00,184
She's a little upset, they've got some big money problems.

692
00:38:00,218 --> 00:38:01,122
- Well can't her parents help out?

693
00:38:01,157 --> 00:38:03,033
I mean I know that Paul is an orphan.

694
00:38:03,068 --> 00:38:04,597
- No, her father left when she was kid,

695
00:38:04,632 --> 00:38:06,856
mother died a couple of years ago.

696
00:38:06,892 --> 00:38:10,298
Yeah, it's kinda hard to watch them struggle,

697
00:38:11,376 --> 00:38:12,105
don't you think?

698
00:38:12,140 --> 00:38:14,955
(light hearted music)

699
00:38:14,990 --> 00:38:18,604
- The dead line was noon Mr. Rodericks.

700
00:38:18,639 --> 00:38:21,246
We went ahead and book the room with another party.

701
00:38:21,281 --> 00:38:23,262
If you'll remember the deposit is nonrefundable.

702
00:38:23,297 --> 00:38:25,486
- But I was helping to save a man's life.

703
00:38:25,521 --> 00:38:28,093
I'm an hour late and you're keeping my $1,000?

704
00:38:28,128 --> 00:38:29,275
- My managers on vacation.

705
00:38:29,310 --> 00:38:34,037
I'm not authorized to refund nonrefundable deposits.

706
00:38:34,071 --> 00:38:36,921
- Don't ever get sick and come to my hospital Haswell.

707
00:38:38,242 --> 00:38:39,146
(bell dings)

708
00:38:39,181 --> 00:38:40,049
(light hearted music)

709
00:38:40,085 --> 00:38:41,092
- [Woman] I'll get the door.

710
00:38:41,127 --> 00:38:42,969
- [Man] Sure this stuff is okay in the hall?

711
00:38:43,004 --> 00:38:43,525
- [Woman] Oh yeah.

712
00:38:44,325 --> 00:38:45,194
- How's it going guys?

713
00:38:45,229 --> 00:38:49,191
(light hearted music)

714
00:38:49,225 --> 00:38:49,817
- [Man] Alright.

715
00:38:49,851 --> 00:38:50,685
- [Man] No it look great.

716
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:56,282
(chattering) (light hearted music)

717
00:39:01,773 --> 00:39:02,711
- Ta da.

718
00:39:02,746 --> 00:39:03,963
- [Woman] Oh hey Art.

719
00:39:03,997 --> 00:39:06,327
- Hey, does anyone need some coffee to calm their nerves?

720
00:39:06,361 --> 00:39:09,732
- Hey Art I'm so glad you could come.

721
00:39:09,767 --> 00:39:11,226
What do you think?

722
00:39:11,262 --> 00:39:14,355
- Oh wow does she know that you're wearing a tux?

723
00:39:14,390 --> 00:39:15,571
- Shhh.

724
00:39:15,606 --> 00:39:17,726
(light hearted music)

725
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:19,463
- Come on here.

726
00:39:19,499 --> 00:39:21,584
We are getting married today .

727
00:39:21,619 --> 00:39:24,468
(light hearted music)

728
00:39:24,503 --> 00:39:26,728
- Hey, hey, hey everybody.

729
00:39:27,979 --> 00:39:29,231
(knocking)

730
00:39:29,266 --> 00:39:30,309
Can I come in?

731
00:39:30,343 --> 00:39:31,802
I need my toothbrush.

732
00:39:36,391 --> 00:39:37,086
- Now don't peak.

733
00:39:38,546 --> 00:39:41,014
You're not supposed to see the bride before the ceremony.

734
00:39:41,048 --> 00:39:42,404
- But I've already seen you in the dress

735
00:39:42,438 --> 00:39:43,690
if that's what you mean.

736
00:39:44,906 --> 00:39:47,895
- Ah, Paul, I have a confession to make,

737
00:39:47,930 --> 00:39:53,144
I um, I sold the dress to pay for your tuition

738
00:39:53,179 --> 00:39:55,090
and I feel so terrible

739
00:39:55,124 --> 00:39:57,453
and I know that you sold your dad's watch

740
00:39:57,487 --> 00:39:58,496
to pay for the hotel

741
00:39:58,530 --> 00:40:00,338
and now we don't have a dress or a watch...

742
00:40:00,374 --> 00:40:01,242
- Guess what, guess what?

743
00:40:01,277 --> 00:40:03,223
I have a confession too.

744
00:40:03,258 --> 00:40:04,682
The hotel stole my deposit

745
00:40:04,718 --> 00:40:06,003
and gave the room to somebody else.

746
00:40:06,039 --> 00:40:07,150
- What?

747
00:40:07,186 --> 00:40:12,573
- But, but that was after I got a call from Lauren

748
00:40:12,607 --> 00:40:13,580
at Wedding Belles.

749
00:40:14,971 --> 00:40:17,231
(gasps)

750
00:40:17,265 --> 00:40:20,115
(chuckling) (gasping)

751
00:40:20,149 --> 00:40:21,192
Not bad huh?

752
00:40:24,077 --> 00:40:25,399
- I love you.

753
00:40:25,432 --> 00:40:26,440
Hi everybody.

754
00:40:26,475 --> 00:40:27,448
- [All] Hi.

755
00:40:28,734 --> 00:40:31,237
(knocking)

756
00:40:32,107 --> 00:40:32,836
- Hi everybody.

757
00:40:32,871 --> 00:40:33,670
- [Woman] Hi Doctor.

758
00:40:33,704 --> 00:40:34,956
- Paul I know, I'm sorry, I'm early

759
00:40:34,991 --> 00:40:39,683
but, well, Art and I wanted to give you a wedding present.

760
00:40:39,718 --> 00:40:42,082
- You can't give away something this precious.

761
00:40:44,167 --> 00:40:46,773
(chattering)

762
00:40:55,567 --> 00:40:56,679
- Oh hey.

763
00:40:56,714 --> 00:40:58,939
- Laura hurry I can't wait to see you in this dress.

764
00:40:58,973 --> 00:40:59,877
Come on.

765
00:40:59,912 --> 00:41:01,615
- That's right, we are in a hurry Paul

766
00:41:01,649 --> 00:41:03,040
we have to be somewhere in 15 minutes.

767
00:41:03,074 --> 00:41:04,187
- But the minister isn't here yet.

768
00:41:04,221 --> 00:41:05,125
- He's been detained.

769
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:06,828
- Yeah he was taken hostage.

770
00:41:06,863 --> 00:41:07,767
- What?

771
00:41:09,782 --> 00:41:10,651
What did you guys do?

772
00:41:10,686 --> 00:41:12,806
- Yeah 30 years I've been driving cab.

773
00:41:12,841 --> 00:41:13,988
Save, save, save for what?

774
00:41:14,023 --> 00:41:14,996
A tombstone?

775
00:41:15,031 --> 00:41:15,969
- Well where we gonna go?

776
00:41:16,004 --> 00:41:17,394
- The Parisenne room at the St. George.

777
00:41:17,429 --> 00:41:18,436
Now you wait til you see--

778
00:41:18,472 --> 00:41:20,557
- Come on Art don't give the whole thing away.

779
00:41:20,592 --> 00:41:22,747
- I can't believe this is happening.

780
00:41:22,781 --> 00:41:25,007
- [Laura] Ready everybody?

781
00:41:26,674 --> 00:41:29,594
(romantic music)

782
00:41:38,353 --> 00:41:40,437
(thuds)

783
00:41:41,377 --> 00:41:43,080
(gasping)

784
00:41:43,115 --> 00:41:46,104
(coffee splashes)

785
00:41:53,959 --> 00:41:55,001
- Oh my God.

786
00:41:56,634 --> 00:41:58,720
My God what have I done?

787
00:42:03,239 --> 00:42:03,934
- Paul,

788
00:42:06,089 --> 00:42:08,070
I'm marrying you not the dress.

789
00:42:09,425 --> 00:42:12,623
Now I am the happiest woman in the world today

790
00:42:12,657 --> 00:42:14,708
and nothing is going to change that.

791
00:42:18,810 --> 00:42:20,512
Give me two seconds everyone.

792
00:42:20,548 --> 00:42:23,294
(romantic music)

793
00:42:47,831 --> 00:42:50,438
(gentle music)

794
00:42:55,375 --> 00:42:57,356
Hey Travis long time no see.

795
00:42:57,390 --> 00:42:59,129
- Hey, are you married yet

796
00:42:59,163 --> 00:43:00,380
or is there still a chance for me?

797
00:43:00,413 --> 00:43:02,673
- I am so married it's disgusting.

798
00:43:02,707 --> 00:43:03,404
Where's our Zoey?

799
00:43:03,437 --> 00:43:05,557
I haven't seen her in months.

800
00:43:05,593 --> 00:43:06,914
- I have no idea.

801
00:43:08,095 --> 00:43:10,181
She's gone without a trace.

802
00:43:10,216 --> 00:43:11,919
- Wow.

803
00:43:11,954 --> 00:43:15,012
She was so in love with you it wasn't funny.

804
00:43:15,047 --> 00:43:17,133
- How is it that everybody could see that but me?

805
00:43:18,418 --> 00:43:20,677
- Maybe you need to get yourself some glasses.

806
00:43:20,712 --> 00:43:23,457
(gentle music)

807
00:43:44,243 --> 00:43:46,849
