My daughter's wedding is the day after tomorrow

906
00:48:59,350 --> 00:49:00,913
and her dress was being altered.

907
00:49:00,949 --> 00:49:02,756
I think it was given to you by mistake.

908
00:49:02,790 --> 00:49:05,501
- Well I don't have the dresses here.

909
00:49:05,536 --> 00:49:07,378
They're being stored at the hospital.

910
00:49:07,413 --> 00:49:08,908
It's for a benefit thing.

911
00:49:09,845 --> 00:49:11,444
- Is this your dress?

912
00:49:11,479 --> 00:49:13,912
- I don't know, I mean the dresses were donated

913
00:49:13,948 --> 00:49:15,059
I just picked them up.

914
00:49:18,397 --> 00:49:19,439
It's very, very pretty.

915
00:49:19,473 --> 00:49:21,038
Look at those little pearls.

916
00:49:22,324 --> 00:49:24,027
I think that lace is all handmade.

917
00:49:24,061 --> 00:49:25,695
It's really, it's exquisite.

918
00:49:25,730 --> 00:49:28,232
- Unfortunately it doesn't fit my daughter.

919
00:49:28,268 --> 00:49:29,552
- No, well, um.

920
00:49:31,673 --> 00:49:34,280
I would take you over there but I'm,

921
00:49:34,316 --> 00:49:36,852
I'm busy so I'll just get a pen and paper

922
00:49:36,887 --> 00:49:38,138
and give you directions.

923
00:49:38,173 --> 00:49:40,190
- Here's a pen, just write it on my arm.

924
00:49:47,488 --> 00:49:48,218
- Where?

925
00:49:48,253 --> 00:49:49,156
You've got the phone book here.

926
00:49:49,192 --> 00:49:51,207
Why don't you give me your other arm.

927
00:49:54,127 --> 00:49:55,725
- It's the best secretary in the world.

928
00:49:55,760 --> 00:49:58,332
The only downside is it looks a little idiotic.

929
00:50:03,789 --> 00:50:06,083
- You're the only other person I've met who does this.

930
00:50:07,751 --> 00:50:09,453
I'd take that as a good sign except you're the only person

931
00:50:09,489 --> 00:50:11,783
I've ever met who carries around a spoon.

932
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:13,450
(sighs)

933
00:50:13,486 --> 00:50:18,664
- Um look, why don't I, why don't I just drive over there

934
00:50:18,700 --> 00:50:20,472
and you can follow me okay?

935
00:50:20,507 --> 00:50:21,619
But you take the dress.

936
00:50:21,654 --> 00:50:23,079
- But I thought you were busy?

937
00:50:23,113 --> 00:50:25,442
- Well I lied, I'm just depressed

938
00:50:25,476 --> 00:50:27,806
and I wanted to be left alone.

939
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:30,030
- That's the worst thing you can do if you're depressed.

940
00:50:30,066 --> 00:50:31,317
- I know don't remind me.

941
00:50:32,394 --> 00:50:33,958
It's too depressing.

942
00:50:33,993 --> 00:50:35,870
- I know the feeling.

943
00:50:35,904 --> 00:50:37,365
It's like looking at your life through the wrong end

944
00:50:37,399 --> 00:50:38,233
of a telescope.

945
00:50:39,518 --> 00:50:40,422
I'm Steve.

946
00:50:42,438 --> 00:50:43,516
- I'm Madeline.

947
00:50:51,128 --> 00:50:52,171
This one it?

948
00:50:53,248 --> 00:50:57,385
- No it's ah, it's the wrong style.

949
00:51:00,442 --> 00:51:04,197
Well, no dress, no preacher and no flowers.

950
00:51:06,213 --> 00:51:08,332
She'll keep the groom under house arrest.

951
00:51:08,368 --> 00:51:09,862
- Why no preacher and no flowers?

952
00:51:09,897 --> 00:51:12,052
- Ah the preacher has laryngitis,

953
00:51:12,086 --> 00:51:14,380
florist thought it was next Saturday.

954
00:51:15,701 --> 00:51:17,716
And you stole my dress.

955
00:51:17,752 --> 00:51:18,655
- Hey.

956
00:51:21,401 --> 00:51:22,861
Look, is this it?

957
00:51:24,008 --> 00:51:24,911
This one?

958
00:51:28,318 --> 00:51:29,361
- That's it.

959
00:51:31,863 --> 00:51:32,766
Thank God.

960
00:51:33,879 --> 00:51:35,720
- I'm a landscape architect,

961
00:51:35,756 --> 00:51:37,493
I could help you with the flowers.

962
00:51:37,528 --> 00:51:39,613
Only I'm very expensive.

963
00:51:39,649 --> 00:51:41,768
- That's okay I'm rich

964
00:51:41,804 --> 00:51:43,264
and I'm desperate.

965
00:51:45,036 --> 00:51:48,407
- I'm not really very expensive.

966
00:51:48,442 --> 00:51:50,422
- I'm not rich, I'm just desperate.

967
00:51:50,458 --> 00:51:53,343
(laughing)

968
00:51:53,378 --> 00:51:55,567
- [Steve] Oh, Kathy I can't do this.

969
00:51:55,602 --> 00:51:58,348
Trying to thread a needle with boxing gloves on.

970
00:51:58,383 --> 00:52:00,260
- I can get it daddy.

971
00:52:00,295 --> 00:52:03,075
I was just trying to make you feel useful.

972
00:52:03,109 --> 00:52:05,577
(laughing)

973
00:52:07,316 --> 00:52:08,219
I miss mom today.

974
00:52:11,069 --> 00:52:12,251
- Everyday honey.

975
00:52:12,286 --> 00:52:14,232
(tapping)

976
00:52:14,267 --> 00:52:16,283
- Now your dad said you wanted something,

977
00:52:16,318 --> 00:52:17,291
something different so.

978
00:52:17,325 --> 00:52:18,471
- Wow I love it!

979
00:52:19,549 --> 00:52:21,426
White is so, white.

