00:52:44,713 --> 00:52:46,625
- Mommy I'm so hungry.

988
00:52:46,660 --> 00:52:47,772
Can we get some pizza?

989
00:52:50,761 --> 00:52:53,021
- Sure, would you like to order it yourself?

990
00:52:54,028 --> 00:52:56,844
(phone ringing)

991
00:52:58,859 --> 00:52:59,763
- Hello?

992
00:53:00,458 --> 00:53:01,849
Hi daddy.

993
00:53:01,883 --> 00:53:03,136
When are you coming home?

994
00:53:05,047 --> 00:53:06,264
He wants to talk to you.

995
00:53:13,909 --> 00:53:14,882
- Mmhmm?

996
00:53:14,918 --> 00:53:17,419
- Why haven't you been answering my calls.

997
00:53:17,455 --> 00:53:19,505
- This is the last time you're gonna hear my voice.

998
00:53:19,540 --> 00:53:22,391
My lawyer will call you sometime this week.

999
00:53:22,424 --> 00:53:23,954
- Who did you get?

1000
00:53:23,990 --> 00:53:25,518
- Your worst nightmare.

1001
00:53:25,553 --> 00:53:28,021
- You're doing something you're really gonna regret.

1002
00:53:28,055 --> 00:53:32,539
- No, Rob what I regret is having married you.

1003
00:53:38,691 --> 00:53:41,820
(knocking)

1004
00:53:41,854 --> 00:53:44,114
- Look what I found in my truck.

1005
00:53:44,148 --> 00:53:45,921
- It's deja vu all over again.

1006
00:53:47,936 --> 00:53:49,744
- I think that dress has your name on it.

1007
00:53:49,779 --> 00:53:51,586
Will you wear it at the benefit?

1008
00:53:51,620 --> 00:53:55,097
- Well I don't know, it'll take a little work.

1009
00:53:57,807 --> 00:53:59,302
A lot of work.

1010
00:54:02,464 --> 00:54:03,890
- So ah...

1011
00:54:05,106 --> 00:54:06,185
- Thank you.

1012
00:54:06,219 --> 00:54:07,748
- Sure.

1013
00:54:07,783 --> 00:54:09,555
Um I wanted to ask you something.

1014
00:54:09,590 --> 00:54:13,066
- No Steve, no I'm getting a divorce now.

1015
00:54:13,101 --> 00:54:16,229
And frankly, no offense I am allergic to men right now.

1016
00:54:16,264 --> 00:54:19,982
I don't want a male parakeet under this roof.

1017
00:54:20,018 --> 00:54:22,033
I don't want a mosquito with male paraphernalia.

1018
00:54:23,180 --> 00:54:24,639
- Well if I'd been trying to pick you up

1019
00:54:24,675 --> 00:54:28,012
that would have been the sexiest response I can imagine.

1020
00:54:28,046 --> 00:54:30,583
- Well weren't you trying to, pick me up?

1021
00:54:31,521 --> 00:54:33,781
- It's not that, you're very,

1022
00:54:35,241 --> 00:54:36,944
you know you're very beautiful.

1023
00:54:40,142 --> 00:54:43,374
Truth is my wife was the love of my life

1024
00:54:43,408 --> 00:54:46,120
and I don't anticipate recovering from losing her.

1025
00:54:47,683 --> 00:54:49,596
- Well I understand that.

1026
00:54:49,630 --> 00:54:51,854
- So now having cheered you up.

1027
00:54:51,890 --> 00:54:54,149
What I was actually gonna ask you,

1028
00:54:54,184 --> 00:54:56,616
I'm running a job that needs a landscape architect

1029
00:54:56,651 --> 00:54:59,745
and, let me give you the number in case you decide

1030
00:54:59,779 --> 00:55:00,648
you're interested.

1031
00:55:00,683 --> 00:55:03,151
(gentle music)

1032
00:55:15,419 --> 00:55:17,992
(gentle music)

1033
00:55:34,223 --> 00:55:37,456
- Hello this is Madeline Carter, I'm a landscape architect,

1034
00:55:37,490 --> 00:55:39,610
I'm calling at Steve Blaine's suggestion.

1035
00:55:47,014 --> 00:55:50,038
- My neighborhood association is considering picketing me.

1036
00:55:50,073 --> 00:55:52,783
They say I've gotta tidy this place up.

1037
00:55:52,819 --> 00:55:53,966
- You might buy a rake.

1038
00:55:55,113 --> 00:55:58,032
You could have told me this was for you.

1039
00:56:00,673 --> 00:56:02,758
- I was afraid you'd get the wrong impression.

1040
00:56:07,451 --> 00:56:08,320
So what do you think?

1041
00:56:08,355 --> 00:56:12,977
- Well, I think it has possibilities.

1042
00:56:13,013 --> 00:56:16,280
(light hearted music)

1043
00:56:18,991 --> 00:56:20,624
- [Steve] Hey.

1044
00:56:20,658 --> 00:56:22,188
- [Madeline] Hey.

1045
00:56:22,223 --> 00:56:23,648
- Just lost half an hour looking for this.

1046
00:56:23,682 --> 00:56:25,559
- Oh I'm sorry I--

1047
00:56:25,594 --> 00:56:27,679
- I hope you're a good climber.

1048
00:56:27,714 --> 00:56:28,513
- Hey!

1049
00:56:29,660 --> 00:56:31,711
This entire pile has to move alright?

1050
00:56:31,746 --> 00:56:32,824
- [Woman] Yeah.

1051
00:56:32,858 --> 00:56:34,909
- We gotta do that now and then we gotta put down

1052
00:56:34,944 --> 00:56:35,396
